@startuml service_async
!theme plain

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceParticipantPadding 30
skinparam sequenceBoxPadding 10
skinparam noteFontSize 11

title ROS 2 Service Communication (Async Client)

participant "Client Node\n(SingleThreadedExecutor)" as Client
participant "Executor" as CExec
participant "Server Node" as Server

== Initialization ==

Client -> Client : create_client(\nComputeTrajectory,\n"compute_trajectory")
Client -> Client : wait_for_service()
note right of Client : Blocks until\nserver is discovered

Server -> Server : create_service(\nComputeTrajectory,\n"compute_trajectory",\ncallback)

== Sending Request (Async) ==

Client -> Client : request = ComputeTrajectory.Request()
Client -> Server : call_async(request)
note right of Client : Returns a **Future**\nimmediately (non-blocking)
Client -> Client : future.add_done_callback(\n_response_callback)

note over Client : Node continues spinning.\nExecutor processes\nother callbacks freely.

... Server processes request ...

Server -> Server : _service_callback(request, response)
note right of Server : Populates response\nfields and returns

Server --> Client : response (via Future)

CExec -> Client : _response_callback(future)
note right of Client : future.result()\nretrieves the response

@enduml
